\section{Courtesan}
\label{courtesan}
d3 7
a9 19
Courtesanship is a social skill designed expressly to satisfy the
needs of lonely or status conscious people.  A master courtesan will
be an accomplished musician, able to play at least one woodwind or
string instrument.  The master will also be able to sing recite and
compose stories and legends, perform mime, act out skits and dance.
The consummate courtesan is also the master of proper dress, and
attractive appearance and is able to simulate a great range of
emotions.

The abilities attendant to the courtesan skill are usable by such a
character in situations not covered by the following rules, as are
those of the troubadour skill (\S\ref{troubadour}).  The GM should
improvise and allow a courtesan character to use their skill in
appropriate instances. If, for instance, the party is at the mercy of
a homely witch of indeterminate age, a male courtesan should be able
to charm her and at least win his companions' lives if he plays it
right.

A courtier is a male courtesan.
d13 10
a22 17
A courtesan character must pay an additional Experience Point
increment of 10\% to increase their Rank in the skill when:
\begin{enumerate}
\setlength\itemsep{0pt}
\item   Their Manual Dexterity is less than 12
\item   Their Agility is less than 15
\item   Their Physical Beauty is  less  than  15
\item   They are death-aspected
\end{enumerate}
A courtesan character decreases the Experience Point cost to increase
their Rank by an increment of 10\% when:
\begin{enumerate}
\setlength\itemsep{0pt}
\item   Their Agility is greater than 22
\item   Their Physical Beauty is greater than 20
\item   They are life-aspected
\end{enumerate}
d27 103
a129 64
\subsubsection{A courtesan acquires one ability per Rank.}

The character begins with one of the following abilities at Rank 0.
All acquired abilities can be performed skillfully.
\begin{enumerate}
\setlength\itemsep{0pt}
\item Play a woodwind instrument (e.g., flute)
\item Play a string instrument (e.g., mandolin, lute, etc.)
\item Sing
\item Recite stories and legends
\item Compose stories and legends
\item Perform mime
\item Act out skits
\item Tell jokes
\item Dance
\item Dress well (e.g., formally)
\item Dress seductively
\item Appear attractive (by other culture's standards)
\item Simulate wide range of emotions
\item Imitate accents
\end{enumerate}
A courtesan may gain additional abilities after achieving Rank 10 by
the expenditure of 500 Experience Points per ability.

\subsubsection{A courtesan may attempt to seduce a being with whom the
courtesan is sexually compatible.}

The courtesan must arrange a meeting with their intended paramour,
either alone or with persons who will not interfere while the
courtesan practices their wiles.  The GM rolls percentile dice: the
courtesan's base chance of success is equal to the courtesan's
(Physical Beauty + 10 \x Rank).  The GM then modifies the success
chance, dependent on the feelings and condition of the seductee.

If the roll is equal to or less than the success percentage, the
seductee is infatuated with the courtesan and will retire with the
seductor to a more private place.  If the roll is greater than the
success percentage, the outcome will depend on how great the roll is.
A roll close to the success percentage calls for anything from ``the
body is willing but the spirit needs more convincing'' to polite
refusal, while a high roll can result in anything from mild
embarrassment to the courtesan to violent consequences.  Player
characters are not bound by the result when a courtesan uses their
skill on them.

\subsubsection{A courtesan's fee for services is dependent upon Rank and
gender.}

A courtier will receive (25 + Rank squared) Silver Pennies for a
night's work.  A courtesan will receive (25 + (Rank + 1) squared)
Silver Pennies for the same job.  The distaff side will do better at
this profession in a male-dominated society.  The pay rates are
reversed in a matriarchy.  A courtesan is expected to charge a lower
\emph{per diam} if hired for consecutive evenings.

\subsubsection{A courtesan's social position has peculiar advantages and
disadvantages.}

A master courtesan is equally welcome at a royal ball and at the
lowest dive in town.  At the same time, a courtesan can be prevented
from practicing their skill or imprisoned if the local authorities are
so inclined.  A courtesan should keep in mind that it helps to provide
services at a discount or for free and to bribe the right people to
ensure freedom of action.
@


