Courtesan, and their male counterparts, Couriers, are trained in the
skills needed for the courtly life.  Court life and High Society
involve status and rank, where the forms of dress and behaviour must
be strictly followed if a person wishes to fit in and exert influence.
While a courtesan and troubadour have similar abilities, a troubadour
is more at home with the people, where as a courtesan is at home with
the Lords and Ladies of the land.

A courtesan will be an accomplished musician, able to play at least
one woodwind or string instrument.  They will also be able to sing
recite and compose stories and legends, perform mime, act out skits
and dance.
